## Quick Start

\`\`\`bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Set up environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your database URL and JWT secret
<% if (provider === 'mongodb') { %>
# Push database schema (MongoDB uses db push instead of migrations)
npx prisma db push
<% } else { %>
# Run database migrations
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
<% } -%>

# Start development server
npm run dev
\`\`\`

## API Documentation

Once the server is running, visit:

- **Swagger UI**: [http://localhost:3000/api/docs](http://localhost:3000/api/docs)
- **Health Check**: [http://localhost:3000/health](http://localhost:3000/health)

## Available Endpoints

<% for (const model of models) { -%>
### <%= model.name %>

<%
const singleId = model.selectors?.find((s) => s.kind === 'id' && s.fields.length === 1);
const compositeId = model.selectors?.find((s) => s.kind === 'id' && s.fields.length > 1);
const singleUnique = model.selectors?.find((s) => s.kind === 'unique' && s.fields.length === 1);
const compositeUnique = model.selectors?.find((s) => s.kind === 'unique' && s.fields.length > 1);
const resolvedSelector = singleId || compositeId || singleUnique || compositeUnique;
const selectorPath = resolvedSelector ? '/' + resolvedSelector.fields.map((f) => `:${f}`).join('/') : null;
-%>
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %>\` | List all |
| POST | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %>\` | Create |
<% if (selectorPath) { -%>
| GET | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %><%= selectorPath %>\` | Get by key |
| PUT | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %><%= selectorPath %>\` | Full update |
| PATCH | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %><%= selectorPath %>\` | Partial update |
| DELETE | \`/api/<%= h.pluralize(h.toCamelCase(model.name)) %><%= selectorPath %>\` | Delete |
<% } -%>

<% } -%>
